# Lala Rente Project - Cursor Rules

## High-level Architecture
- Next.js App Router app in lalarente-app
- Mobile via Capacitor (Android project present)
- Supabase backend, strongly typed via src/types/supabase.ts
- Supabase client in src/lib/supabase.ts

## Coding/Architecture Guidelines
- DB-first approach - respect Supabase schema and RLS
- UI components live under src/components (keep outside route folders)
- Routes in src/app
- Global auth and mobile UX hooks initialized in src/app/layout.tsx
- ESLint uses Next core-web-vitals + TS
- Tailwind configured with brand palette

## UI/UX Standards
- Tailwind theme with Indian-inspired palette (sa-green, sa-gold, sa-blue)
- Mobile-hardening in layout (viewport lock, safe-area, selection disabled for native)
- Follow existing component patterns and file locations

## Tools/MCP Requirements
- Use Supabase MCP to read tables, functions, RLS, advisors before any change
- Validate queries against Supabase JS SDK patterns
- Provide GitBash commands for user to run; do not auto-execute

## Development Workflow
- Phase tasks per roadmap (when present)
- For new features: scaffold UI (outside app), mock data, then wire backend
- Run dev server locally, resolve TS/lint before deployment

## Testing/QA
- Type-safe calls via supabase client and Database types
- Prefer exact types (no any)
- Add indices for FKs if needed
- Avoid perf anti-patterns in RLS policies
- Keep code readable and consistent

## Security/Privacy
- RLS enabled; add missing policies before exposing features
- Avoid mutable function search_path; enable leaked password protection
- Public signup allowed with verification and duplicate checks (email/ID); enforce business validations during registration

## Assistant Behavior Rules
- Never deviate from these rules or phased goals without explicit confirmation
- Reference existing files/components before proposing code
- Break complex tasks into small, actionable plans and seek approval before edits
- Keep responses concise; avoid generic suggestions
- Check prior work to avoid regressions

## Key Schema Facts
**Tables:** profiles, properties, property_assignments, leases, payments, maintenance_requests, inspections, messages
**Enums:** user_role, property_status, payment_status, maintenance_status, inspection_type
**Storage:** buckets/objects present

## Known Issues to Address
- RLS policies missing for: inspections, leases, maintenance_requests, messages, property_assignments
- Multiple permissive policies and initplan issues on profiles, properties, payments
- Many unindexed FKs flagged (need indexes on FK columns)
- Several public functions flagged for mutable search_path (set stable search_path)
